# HellBot

HellBot is designed to enhance music playback on your Discord server.

## Usage

To use HellBot, you must install the latest 64-bit version of Java.

Steps:
1. To launch HellBot, open a terminal window in the directory where the application is located.
2. Execute the command: "java -jar filename". For example "java -jar hell-bot-0.4.1.jar".

On first run, you will need to:
• Enter your Discord API key.
• Choose the type of database you wish to use:
  If you choose the H2 database, it will be automatically created and store the authorization data.
  If you choose PostgreSQL, ensure you have created an empty database beforehand and have the connection details ready.

## Features

• Hosts yourself
• Fast loading of songs
• Supports online radio/streams, including Youtube
• Supports local files
• Save playback history

## Supported formats powered by Lavaplayer.
The set of sources where LavaPlayer can load tracks from is easily extensible, but the ones currently included by default are:
• YouTube
• SoundCloud
• Twitch streams
• Local files
• HTTP URLs

The file formats that LavaPlayer can currently handle are (relevant for file/url sources):
• MP3
• FLAC
• WAV
• Matroska/WebM (AAC, Opus or Vorbis codecs)
• MP4/M4A (AAC codec)
• OGG streams (Opus, Vorbis and FLAC codecs)
• AAC streams

